#: .\m_armor.json
msgid "UN helmet"
msgid_plural "UN helmets"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'UN helmet'}
#: .\m_armor.json
msgid ""
"A heavy helmet that provides excellent protection from all sorts of damage."
"  It is labeled as the advanced combat helmet. It is emblazoned with the "
"blue globe logo of the UN. A coveted prize amongst certain survivalist "
"types."
msgstr ""

#: .\m_armor.json
msgid "UN security vest"
msgid_plural "UN security vests"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'UN security vest'}
#: .\m_armor.json
msgid ""
"A bullet-resistant vest used by UN security forces deployed to the New "
"England Exlcusion zone by various obscure benefactors. Although not the best"
" ballistic protection, it is more than sufficient for most of the hazards of"
" the Exclusion Zone."
msgstr ""

#: .\m_items.json
msgid "Sailor Fuku shirt"
msgid_plural "Sailor Fuku shirts"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Sailor Fuku shirt'}
#: .\m_items.json
msgid ""
"A short-sleeved cotton shirt, similar to the sailor fuku often seen in Japan"
" or anime."
msgstr ""

#: .\m_items.json
msgid "Fuku Skirt"
msgid_plural "Fuku Skirts"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Fuku Skirt'}
#: .\m_items.json
msgid ""
"A short, breezy cotton skirt.  Easy to move in, but only has a single small "
"pocket. Commonly seen in Japan or anime."
msgstr ""

#: .\m_items.json
msgid "Reinforced French maid clothes"
msgid_plural "Reinforced French maid clothes"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Reinforced French maid clothes', 'str_pl':
#. 'Reinforced French maid clothes'}
#: .\m_items.json
msgid ""
"The French maid dress, blue with a frilly white apron. This particular "
"version has been reinfored with Kevlar, thus turning a once near useless "
"maid dress into a genuine combat article."
msgstr ""

#: .\m_items.json
msgid "Reinforced kimono"
msgid_plural "Reinforced kimonos"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Reinforced kimono'}
#: .\m_items.json
msgid ""
"A traditional, ankle-length Japanese robe, wrapped around the body with a "
"sash. This particular version has been reinfored with Kevlar."
msgstr ""

#: .\m_items.json
msgid "Reinforced yukata"
msgid_plural "Reinforced yukatas"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Reinforced yukata'}
#: .\m_items.json
msgid ""
"An easy-to-wear, breezy robe secured with a sash.  Essentially Japanese "
"pajamas.  Great for summer nights. This particular version has been "
"reinfored with Kevlar."
msgstr ""

#: .\m_items.json
msgid "Reinforced Fuku Skirt"
msgid_plural "Reinforced Fuku Skirts"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Reinforced Fuku Skirt'}
#: .\m_items.json
msgid ""
"A short, breezy cotton skirt.  Easy to move in, but only has a single small "
"pocket. Commonly seen in Japan or anime. This particular version has been "
"reinfored with Kevlar."
msgstr ""

#: .\m_items.json
msgid "Reinforced Sailor Fuku shirt"
msgid_plural "Reinforced Sailor Fuku shirts"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Reinforced Sailor Fuku shirt'}
#: .\m_items.json
msgid ""
"A short-sleeved cotton shirt, similar to the sailor fuku often seen in Japan"
" or anime. This particular version has been reinfored with Kevlar."
msgstr ""

#: .\m_items.json
msgid "pair of reinforced stockings"
msgid_plural "pairs of reinforced stockings"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'pair of reinforced stockings', 'str_pl': 'pairs
#. of reinforced stockings'}
#: .\m_items.json
msgid ""
"Long cotton socks that reach above the knees to help protect from the cold. "
"These particular versions have been reinforced with kevlar."
msgstr ""

#: .\m_items.json
msgid "powered exoskeleton"
msgid_plural "powered exoskeletons"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'powered exoskeleton'}
#: .\m_items.json
msgid ""
"An articulated frame that attaches to a user's back. It allows one to lift "
"considerably more weight than one normally could, although it has a high "
"encumbrance."
msgstr ""

#: .\mak_rangedweaps.json
msgid "motorized crossbow"
msgid_plural "motorized crossbows"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#: .\mak_rangedweaps.json
msgid ""
"A modified version of the classic crossbow which utilizes stones as "
"projectiles instead of the traditional quarrel.  Uses UPS power and an "
"electric motor to activate the crossbow."
msgstr ""

#: .\mak_rangedweaps.json
msgctxt "gun_type_type"
msgid "rifle"
msgstr ""

#: .\mak_rangedweaps.json
msgid "large airgun"
msgid_plural "large airguns"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#: .\mak_rangedweaps.json
msgid ""
"A homemade compressed air coilgun gun, using electromagnets and compressed "
"air to accelerate a ferromagnetic projectile to high velocity.  Generally "
"too heavy to be used by a single person."
msgstr ""

#: .\mak_rangedweaps.json
msgid "large airgun magazine"
msgid_plural "large airgun magazines"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'large airgun magazine'}
#: .\mak_rangedweaps.json
msgid ""
"An improvised magazine for use with a heavy airgun rifle.  Little more than "
"a tin can, spring and some duct tape it is awkward to reload and not "
"especially reliable."
msgstr ""

#: .\mak_rangedweaps.json
msgid "mounted heavy coilgun"
msgstr ""

#: .\mak_rangedweaps.json
msgid "Magnetic-Accelerated BB gun"
msgid_plural "Magnetic-Accelerated BB guns"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#: .\mak_rangedweaps.json
msgid ""
"Popular among children.  It's fairly accurate, but BBs deal nearly no "
"damage. This one has been outfitted with a series of magnetic coils to "
"accelerate BBs to a high velocity."
msgstr ""

#: .\modinfo.json
msgid "Add Bandits Extended+"
msgstr ""

#. ~ Description for Add Bandits Extended+
#: .\modinfo.json
msgid ""
"Modified by Malkeus, Further modified with new custom content by Jolmar7 "
"with lots of new added things. Adds bands of non-NPCs type of hostile and "
"friendly armed humans that carry weapons, ammo, that patrol the wastelands "
"looking for things to kill, each with a custom AI."
msgstr ""

